Philippines Sets 40 Billion Pesos Daily Limit for Retail Bonds

-- B y   M a x   E s t a y o
-- 
2011-10-10T06:31:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/philippines-sets-40-billion-pesos-daily-limit-for-retail-bonds.html
The  Philippines  set a limit to sell
a total 40 billion pesos of retail treasury bonds daily, Deputy
Treasurer Eduardo Mendiola said in  Manila  today.  The government will sell as much as 20 billion pesos each
of 10- and 15-year bonds targeted at individuals in an offering
that will end on Oct. 17, Mendiola said. It raised 20 billion
pesos from the interest rate-setting auction of the bonds today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Max Estayo in Manila at 
 mestayo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cecilia Yap at 
 cyap19@bloomberg.net  